title: Switch canary workflow to point to a newly deployed CloudFormation stack

labels.name: needs-review
labels.description: This issue/pr needs review from an internal developer.

body:
## Motivation and Context
Let canary be driven by a new CloudFormation stack to a new account. Historically, the same canary stack has been shared between `aws-sdk-rust` and `smithy-rs`. Now that we are planning to also run the canary as part of `smithy-rs` CI, we should a separate canary stack deployed to a separate account to not affect one another.

This PR will update the canary workflow to point to the newly deployed canary stack. While doing so, it obviates the need for the environment variables for S3 canary. Instead, it downloads `cdk-outputs.json` (a result of running `npx cdk --app "node build/bin/aws-sdk-rust/canary-only.js" deploy --outputs-file cdk-outputs.json`) and passes it to `canary-runner`.

----

title: Make model filenames consistent as used by our release process

title: Remove stale/duplicate Secrets Manager model
body:
New operations in Secrets Manager are missing, as reported in #1017. It looks like we got into a state where we had two models for Secrets Manager in the aws-models/ directory, and the one with a hyphen has the correct name since that's the name the daily release automation uses. The incorrectly named one was the one that was getting code generated, so Secrets Manager updates weren't flowing.

This PR deletes the stale model so that future releases should have the latest operations. This is safe since they both have identical SDK and service IDs in the model.

title: Port changelog entries from `smithy-rs` 0.54 release
body:
## Motivation and Context
Due to the change to our release process in `smithy-rs` that introduced release branches, not all changelog entries from `smithy-rs` may not make it to `aws-sdk-rust` if multiple `smithy-rs` releases are combined into one. In this instance, the  latest `aws-sdk-rust` release includes both 0.54 and 0.55 of `smithy-rs`, and changelog entries for 0.55 wiped out those for 0.54.

This PR backfills missing those entries from the release of `smithy-rs` 0.54 by manually running [changelogger](https://github.com/awslabs/smithy-rs/tree/main/tools/ci-build/changelogger) against [SDK_CHANGELOG.next.json in 0.54](https://github.com/awslabs/smithy-rs/blob/smithy-rs-release-0.54.x/aws/SDK_CHANGELOG.next.json). Furthermore, it includes a markdown table showing all the crate versions.
